task.summary: Default task

Added tests to tasks app.
Added test that checks to make sure a project's str returns its name
Added test to make sure that projects can be related to each other as superior and subordinate
Changed Project class in tasks.models.py so that projects can be related as subordinate and superior.
In the Task class In tasks.models.py, changed the related_projects feature from a foreignkey to many to many.

In task.tests.test_models, added two tests of the Task classes.
1) Tested whether tasks could be created. 2) Tested whether tasks could be related to projects.
In tasks.tests.test_functional.py, created first functional test (just to see if page pulls up) for the Task Manager
In tasks.tests.test_models.py, added first unit tests for contexts and tasks
In tasks.tests.models.py, added "viewers" as an attribute of tasks and projects, so that others can be given permission to see a project.
In tasks.tests.views.taskdetail, added a test that should require users to be involved with a task to be able to view it.
Changed task and project objects so that they can be assigned to multiple people
In tasks.tests.test_views.py, added some initial tests for the views.
The change in task_manager.models.tasks and .projects where the assigned_to attribute was changed from ForeignKey to ManyToMany broke some of the model tests. Fixing ....
In task_manager.tests.test_views.py, wrote tests for the views Task Detail and Task Update, making sure that unauthorized viewers can't view a task, and that authorized viewers can.
In task_manager.urls, changed the url namespace pointing towards task updates to "task_update"

In task_manager.tests.test_views, wrote two tests for the task creation view 1) testing that a superuser gets a 200 (success) http code when they try to go there 2) testing that anonymous users are redirected to a login page.
In task_manager.tests.test_views, made pep8 edits
In task_manager.tests.test_views, added to do notes
In task_manager.tests.test_views, tests to ensure that unauthoarized users are redirected, and authorized users are not.
In task_manager.templates, fixed the index page (was referring to an attribute of tasks that was changed).
In task_manager.views, changed the project creation view to reflect that the project attribute is now named "under_projects", not "related_projects"
In task_manager.views, changed the project update view to reflect that the project attribute is now named "under_projects", not "related_projects"
In task_manager.templates.update-task.html, updated tag to reflect new url namespace for tasks
In the functional tests in the task manager, switched to StaticLiveServerTestCase
Added a namespace for the django authentication
